Description: Shoulder fragment from a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown, hard fired. Stamp on shoulder with Latin inscription.
Curator's comments: cf. Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine, Oxford 1989, no. 67. A group of eleven or more was found in the Athenian Agora (SS11094ff) Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 59, 29.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1277)
